name: Free Flow Brunch
description:
A one-of-a-kind Free Flow Brunch weekend with our resident chef Linh-San (@sannysfood), marking First-ever resident chef concept in Hanoi. 
Let's celebrate this beautiful autumn breeze with Linh-San, whose hospitality and culinary career started in Denmark. Born and raised in Bulgaria while also having lived in Denmark and Vietnam, Linh-San grew her love for food as she explored the role it plays in each person’s identity and culture. For San, food is emotional, food brings people closer together. 

Linh-San has honed her skills working for some of the best chefs in the countries she has lived in. This coming October, Linh-San will collaborate with Déglacer on the Free Flow Brunch event, inviting you to enjoy a friendly and delicious brunch experience.

The brunch will be served buffet-style, including a variety of food & beverages to choose from: 
- Cold station: Caesar salad, grilled veggies, plenty of homemade bread, butter, rilletes, sun-dried tomatoes, olives, hummus dippings, french toast, ...
- Hot station: Beef Wellington, grilled prawn, sausages, ...
- Dessert: Fruit platter, tiramisu, mini muffin, ...

Limited seats - Reserve now!
location: Déglacer, số 18, Ngõ 268 Ngọc Thuỵ, Long Biên, Hà Nội

name: Family heritage - Collaboration with Chef Nguyen Van Tu
image:
menu.jpg
chu Tu.jpeg
ironchefthai.jpeg
fam heritage ep1.jpg
description:
In this first episode of the "Family Heritage" season, Déglacer is honoured to welcome chef Nguyen Van Tu - Iron Chef Vietnam 2012. Chef Nguyen Van Tu has more than 20 years of expertise in the culinary field. After graduating from Hanoi Tourism College, he began working in well-known hotels such as Hanoi Lake View, Meritus Wesk Lake, and Press Club. He is a well-known European chef in Hanoi, having played a significant role in the success of several major culinary events.

On this special occasion, Chef Hieu and Chef Tu are honoured to send Déglacer's diners a special set menu on November 5, 2023. Enjoy the taste of autumn from these two talented chefs, we hope that customers will have a memorable experience.
For more detailed information about the menu and table reservations, please contact the hotline or send a message to Déglacer so we can assist you as soon as possible.
location: Déglacer, số 18, Ngõ 268 Ngọc Thuỵ, Long Biên, Hà Nội

name: Family heritage - Collaboration with Lucci Nguyen Tuan Anh from USEbar
host: USEbar - 55 Ngo Hue, Hai Ba Trung, Hanoi
description:
FAMILY HERITAGE  EPISODE 2 X LUCCI NGUYEN TUAN ANH FROM USEBAR

Join Déglacer in toasting the much-anticipated episode 2 of the "FAMILY HERITAGE" series of events with two brothers from the same family, chef Ha Hieu and Mr. Nguyen Tuan Anh - founder of USEbar Hanoi.  There was a time when Tuan Anh and Hieu worked together at J.A.F.A restaurant around 2013-2014. Unlike most of his family members,  however, Tuan Anh chose to work in the bartending industry after graduating from high school and he has 8 years of experience in this sector thus far. He used to be a manager at The Haflington, one of Asia's 50 greatest bars in 2023, holding the World Class Champion award Vietnam 2023, after many years of working at some famous bars.

This Family Heritage event will take place at USEBar Hanoi, presenting a novel combination of a menu of unique canapes from Hieu - Déglacer complimented by innovative cocktails created by Tuan Anh and the USEbar crew.

Come and enjoy a special price of 950,000VND/pax
___

USEbar, 55 Ngo Hue, Hai Ba Trung, Hanoi,
Hotline: 035.666.8878 or 097.523.9095
Message Déglacer or USEbar for more info
location: USEbar - 55 Ngo Hue, Hai Ba Trung, Hanoi

name: Fundraising Free Flow Brunch x Keep Vietnam Clean
description:
FUNDRAISING FREE FLOW BRUNCH X KEEP VIETNAM CLEAN 

Celebrate your December with Déglacer and our new friend @keepvietnamclean in an extremely meaningful event - Fundraising Free Flow Brunch. With a mission to promote and inspire sustainable lifestyles and environmental health across Vietnam, Keep Vietnam Clean has engaged 5,244 volunteers, organised 106 clean-up events, collected 314 tons of waste, developed 1,700 m2 of greenspace, recruited 496 citizens to champion environmental improvement, set up 6 demo sites of regenerative farming practices. 

In this event, we invite you to enjoy a new glass of mulled wine with lamb, beef, and fresh seafood plate meals. Déglacer and diners will join forces with Keep Vietnam Clean in fundraising activities for the project "Green Space, Healthy Lifestyle," planting shade trees for almost 900 students and 49 teachers at Phuc Tien Primary School, with 50% of the event profit given to Keep Vietnam Clean.

📍 Fundraising Free Flow Brunch: 850,000++/pax 
📅 From 10:00 - 14:30, November 16-17

We hope to see you at Déglacer!
location: Déglacer, số 18, Ngõ 268 Ngọc Thuỵ, Long Biên, Hà Nội

name:
LONG BIEN INVITES
Deux en un by Chef Hai and Chef Hieu
description:
A new season of events are coming to you - LONG BIEN INVITES. 
Proudly calling Long Bien our home, we welcome guest chefs to Déglacer—a culinary playground for collaboration and innovation. We offer unique, wholesome, and fun dishes to delight our guests.

For our first event, we introduce Chef Hai from Paris in our open kitchen. He will bring fresh culinary experiences with a special à la carte menu themed "𝐃𝐞𝐮𝐱 𝐞𝐧 𝐔𝐧 - Two in One” featuring the same main ingredients prepared in two distinct styles.

Chef Hai, born in Hà Nội, Việt Nam, moved to France at 18. He developed his skills in Michelin-starred restaurants and hosted pop-ups in Paris, showcasing his unique cooking style and creating memorable experiences.

Talk about his cooking style, Hai likes to use classic techniques combined with new ingredients as well as playing around with flavours. His cuisine is mostly French with influences from Việt Nam, Argentina, China, Italy and so much more as it retraces his culinary story.

And Chef Hai is here to tell you all about that. After a decade abroad, now he's back in his beloved hometown, ready to conquer new challenges and bring a little taste of Paris to Hà Nội, alongside with Chef Hieu at Déglacer.

🎶Not only good food and wines, live DJ by Dusan is waiting for you! Come & join us for this amazing event! ❤️‍🔥


🥂Special à la carte menu with natural/organic/sustainable wine pours with love.
✨June 1-2, seatings open from 18-21h 
🥖Reservation recommended!
location: Déglacer, số 18, Ngõ 268 Ngọc Thuỵ, Long Biên, Hà Nội

name:
LONG BIEN INVITES
A Taste of "Home" by Chef Yuni and Chef Hieu
description:
We’re back and couldn’t be more excited to continue our Long Biên series with a new episode. Every event is a chance to bring people together, and this time, we’re truly honored to welcome Chef Sri Wahyuni from Indonesia to Déglacer.

👩‍🍳 Chef Yuni has an incredible journey, with years of experience in both Indonesia and Hong Kong. Her passion for authentic Indonesian cuisine shines through in every dish. Expect bold Southeast Asian flavors, beautifully balanced with global influences. For this event, she’ll be sharing the heart and soul of her hometown, Surabaya, with you all.

"A Taste of Home" - A special À la carte - it’s about comfort, warmth, and the feeling of being surrounded by those you love. Chef Yuni and Chef Hieu will bring the homestyle flavors of Indonesia and France to remind you of those cozy family dinners.

Some lovely wines from Da Loc are ready for ya to sip while devouring tasty dishes from both chefs.
Welcome to our home in Long Biên! Book your table now—this is a one-night-only event, and we can’t wait to share it with you and your loved ones!

📅 Date: Oct 11, 2024
🕠 Time: 5.30PM - 9.30PM
📍 Location: Déglacer - No 18, Lane 268, Ngoc Thuy, Long Bien, Hanoi
location: Déglacer, số 18, Ngõ 268 Ngọc Thuỵ, Long Biên, Hà Nội
